This paper deals with sentiment analysis, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also involves machine learning algorithms such as SVMs, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses a novel similarity measure, which could be relevant to the subfield of clustering and classification (cs.CC).
